Chicken Curry with Green Beans
  --Cook's Country
  
8 (3-5 oz) boneless, skinless chicken thighs, trimmed and cut into 1" chunks
1/2 tsp table salt
1/2 tsp pepper
1 tbsp vegetable oil
8 oz green beans, trimmed and cut on bias into 1" lengths
1 red bell pepper, stemmed, seeded, and sliced thin
1 small onion, minced
3 tbsp curry powder
2 garlic cloves, minced
15 oz can tomato sauce
1 c chicken broth

Pat chicken dry with paper towels and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Heat oil in 12" nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until just smoking. Add chicken and cook until lightly browned, 6-8 min. Using slotted spoon, transfer chicken to large plate; set aside. Add green beans, bell pepper, and onion to fat left in skillet and cook over medium-high heat until onion is softened and beginning to brown, ~4 min. Add curry powder and garlic and cook until fragrant, ~30 s. Stir in tomato sauce, broth, and chicken and bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium and simmer, covered, until chicken is cooked through, ~10 min. Serve.


